summary: Completed frontend testing of navigation changes for Admin vs Demo users. All features working correctly - Admin users see full navigation with Administration section at bottom, Demo users do NOT see Administration section.
passed_tests: Super Admin user sees full navigation: Content Intelligence, My Dashboard, Projects, Notifications, Settings, Help & Documentation
Super Admin sees Administration section at bottom of sidebar (after separator)
Super Admin Administration section contains: Analytics Overview, Advanced Analytics, Financial Analytics, Team Management, All Platform Users, Documentation
Admin user sees full navigation with Administration section
Admin user Administration section contains: Analytics Overview, Advanced Analytics, Financial Analytics, Team Management, Documentation (no All Platform Users - correct for non-platform admin)
Demo User does NOT see Administration section in sidebar - verified
Demo User can access Settings > Team page at /contentry/settings/team
Admin can access /contentry/admin analytics page (System Admin Dashboard)
Navigation from Administration > Team Management goes to /contentry/settings/team - verified
context_for_next_testing_agent: Navigation structure verified for all user types. Super Admin and Admin users see Administration section with analytics and team management features. Demo users correctly do not see Administration section. Team Management page accessible via both Settings > Team and Administration > Team Management routes.
